   "source": [
    "# FeatureEstimationDemo\n",
    "\n",
    "### Read example BIDS data \n",
    "\n",
    "In this demo the basic offline workflow of py_neuromodulation will be demonstrated. For that, the example BIDS dataset in *pyneuromodulation/examples/data/* will be analyzed. \n",
    "The parametrization `nm_settings.json` is stored in the package directory *pyneuromodulation/nm_settings.json*, a `nm_channels.csv` is created given the *channel_type* information from the BIDS data. \n",
    "\n",
    "A projection will be defined based on the *pyneuromodulation/grid_cortex.tsv* and *pyneuromodulation/grid_subcortex.tsv* files. Band power features and sharpwave features will then be estimated and projected to the provided grid. \n",
    "\n",
    "First, necessary modules will be included and the BIDS_PATH and RUN_PATH, the path to the BIDS brainvision run file, will be defined given the example."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "a1959766",

     ]

    "PATH_RUN = os.path.join(BIDS_EXAMPLE_PATH, 'sub-testsub', 'ses-EphysMedOff',\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "32c485cb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Many signal processing and feature estimation parameters are here defined. Most importantly the `setttings[\"methods\"]` tells us which signal processing and features should be estimated: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "652a6ccf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'raw_resampling': True,\n",
       " 'raw_normalization': False,\n",
       " 'feature_normalization': True,\n",
       " 'kalman_filter': True,\n",
       " 're_referencing': True,\n",
       " 'notch_filter': True,\n",
       " 'bandpass_filter': True,\n",
       " 'raw_hjorth': True,\n",
       " 'sharpwave_analysis': True,\n",
       " 'return_raw': False,\n",
       " 'project_cortex': True,\n",
       " 'project_subcortex': False,\n",
       " 'pdc': False,\n",
       " 'dtf': False}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nm_BIDS.settings_wrapper.settings[\"methods\"]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b80afb94",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As defined, data will be **resampled**, **normalized** and **rereferenced** (as defined in the nm_channels) before feature estimation. Then, **bandpower features**, **sharpwave features** and **hjorth parameters** are calculated. Additionally, gamma band features will be Kalman filtered. Since *project_cortex* is set to true, projection to a grid is also enabled. \n",
    "\n",
    "### Grid projection\n",
    "\n",
    "Next we will read the cortical grid, defined in *pyneuromodulation/grid_cortex.tsv*, and calculate the **projection matrix** from individual channels to the grid:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0365da48",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now inspect the individual coordinates, and the projected grid points. Therfore we read first a standard MNI hull, defined in the plot folder:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "a83601cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "PATH_PLOT =os.path.join(os.pardir, 'plots')\n",
    "faces = io.loadmat(os.path.join(PATH_PLOT, 'faces.mat'))\n",
    "vertices = io.loadmat(os.path.join(PATH_PLOT, 'Vertices.mat'))\n",
    "grid = io.loadmat(os.path.join(PATH_PLOT, 'grid.mat'))['grid']\n",
    "x_ecog = vertices['Vertices'][::1,0]\n",
    "y_ecog = vertices['Vertices'][::1,1]\n",
    "z_ecog = vertices['Vertices'][::1,2]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1e4281c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the grid is defined for the left hemisphere, we might switch the x coordinates for right electrodes. Then the ECoG channel coordinates and used grid points are visualized:  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "0e2dad3b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(-79.05561408996581, 79.27910194396972, -116.16637420654297, 83.09801483154297)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1008x648 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cortex_grid = np.array(nm_BIDS.projection.grid_cortex.T)\n",
    "\n",
    "if nm_BIDS.settings_wrapper.settings[\"sess_right\"] is True:\n",
    "    cortex_grid[0,:] = cortex_grid[0,:]*-1\n",
    "    ecog_strip = np.array(nm_BIDS.settings_wrapper.settings[\"coord\"][\"cortex_right\"][\"positions\"]).T\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    ecog_strip = np.array(nm_BIDS.settings_wrapper.settings[\"coord\"][\"cortex_left\"][\"positions\"]).T\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,1, facecolor=(1,1,1), \\\n",
    "                        figsize=(14,9))#, dpi=300)\n",
    "axes.scatter(x_ecog, y_ecog, c=\"gray\", s=0.001)\n",
    "axes.axes.set_aspect('equal', anchor='C')\n",
    "\n",
    "grid_color = nm_BIDS.projection.proj_matrix_cortex.sum(axis=1)\n",
    "pos_ecog = axes.scatter(cortex_grid[0,:],\n",
    "                        cortex_grid[1,:], c=grid_color, \n",
    "                        s=30, alpha=0.8, cmap=\"viridis\", label=\"cortical grid projection\")\n",
    "\n",
    "pos_elec = axes.scatter(ecog_strip[0,:],\n",
    "                        ecog_strip[1,:], c=np.ones(ecog_strip.shape[1]), \n",
    "                        s=50, alpha=0.8, cmap=\"gray\", marker=\"x\", label=\"ecog strip electrode contacts\")\n",
    "axes.legend(loc='best')\n",
    "axes.axis('off')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "948db87b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As visible, only grid points are active (channel data is projected unto them as shown in yellow) within the *max_dist* of every individual channel for the cortical and subcortical grid (as specified in the `nm_settings.json`). \n",
    "\n",
    "Next, the **rereference** and **resample** classes get instantiated, and an acquisition system is simulated by a **generator**:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff3e23c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Feature Estimation \n",
    "\n",
    "Now the used **feature** and **run_analysis** classes are instantiated. Here FIR Filters and Kalman Filters are parametrized. During online feature estimation filters only have to be applied, instead of a repetitive calculatation, which saves computational time. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae4e559f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "Then troughs and peaks are identified, subsequently different features are estimated. "

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "89d21c77",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this example plot, the trough sharpness is visualized for the estimated data batch:"

   "source": [
    "# data is being filtered in get_sharpwave_features\n",
    "\n",
    "data = raw_norm[ch_idx,:]\n",
    "nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.initialize_sw_features() \n",
    "nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.filtered_data = np.convolve(data,\n",
    "                                                nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.filter, mode='same')\n",
    "nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.analyze_waveform()\n",
    "trough_dist = nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.sw_settings[\"detect_troughs\"][\"distance_troughs\"]\n",
    "peak_dist = nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.sw_settings[\"detect_troughs\"][\"distance_peaks\"]    \n",
    "\n",
    "peaks = scipy.signal.find_peaks(nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.filtered_data, distance=peak_dist)[0]\n",
    "troughs = scipy.signal.find_peaks(-nm_BIDS.run_analysis.features.sw_features.filtered_data, distance=trough_dist)[0]\n"
   ]
